## Welcome to Tomaree Aquatic Centre

Tomaree Aquatic Centre is proudly managed by Belgravia Leisure on behalf of Port Stephens council.  
The centre features a 50m outdoor heated pool with up to 8 swimming lanes, shaded heated program/kids pool, shaded wading pool, spiral waterslide, large open lawned areas, free BBQ's and volleyball greens.  


At Tomaree Aquatic Centre, we offer a variety of activites from water based to land based! Ranging from Group Fitness Aqua aerobics classes and Functional Fitness classes to swimming lessons and squad training, swimming club and volleyball!   
  
Whether you are needing an energy boost or your little ones need refueling, our kiosk staff can help satisfy even the hungriest of appetites! With great food, drinks and icecreams, there is something for everyone! Including a range of swimwear and swimming accessories conveniently located just outside of the kiosk!

# Group Fitness

## 

## Group Fitness Classes

Getting started can be daunting and our popular group fitness classes are a great way to help build your confidence. Exercise classes are a great way for you to stay motivated through accountability and social encouragement.   
  
To reach and maintain a healthy weight, we should exercise most days of the week for minimum of 30 minutes, our classes make this easy! With a range of fun and motivating classes there will be a class to suit your individual health and fitness goals.   
  
Group fitness classes are a fun way to exercise and give all members and non-members the opportunity to work out in a group atmosphere with like-minded individuals.   
  
Check out our timetable below for our group fitness offerings -  
[Group Fitness Timetable](/getmedia/d9bbeccb-a65d-412c-b869-996ab0155458/december-aqua_2.pdf)

## Fall in Love with Fitness 

If you love being a part of a community our classes foster a great community environment that make you feel welcome, excited and keep you coming back for more.   
  
Catering to a range of ages and capabilities, we have classes in and out of the water, ranging from strength-based through to wellness training aimed at training your mind as well as the body.  
  
Our classes include Pilates, Yoga, Circuit, Aqua Zumba and Aqua Aerobics. 

### Join Our Group Exercise

For more information on our group exercise classes please click below to view our class timetable.

##  Group Fitness FAQs Expand all 

#####  Professional Group Fitness Instructors 

Our group fitness professionals provide quality instructing to motivate you to work out to the best of your ability. With a wealth of knowledge and experience our group fitness instructors are sure to inspire you to achieve your fitness goals. 

#####  A Variety of Group Workout Classes 

In order to cater to a wide variety of members and non-members alike we offer a plethora of exercise classes. Including all different styles of training, ensuring there is something for everyone to enjoy. 

Whether you are looking to attend our group fitness classes or wanting to supplement your gym program. We have classes ranging from strength-based through to wellness training aimed at training your mind as well as the body.

# Your Membership App

**Active World Logo Update**

Our membership portal, Active World, has a new look! Your app now has a new logo, but there are no changes to the way you use it. 

## 

We believe all our members health & fitness journey should be powered by innovative technology. The Active World app was specifically designed to improve your experience with us! The app will give you greater control of your membership and our programs offered in Centre! 

The Active World app allows you to link your family memberships to manage from the once account and will give you greater visibility of your progress and achievements when visiting us! 

Our staff are here to help! Active World is built to improve communication with our team â€“ so if you need us, we are a click of a button away to start chatting! 

Download the app today to get started and bring your membership into the palm of your hand! 

## 

  
Your Active World self-managed portal will allow you to: 

  * Manage your account details 

  * Update your payment details 

  * Check for your next payment 

  * Buy a new membership 

  * Buy a visit pass 

  * Scan in using a digital access card â€“ for when you forget your pass! 

  * Book into your Group Fitness Classes 

  * View upcoming classes 

  * Advise of us of your GOswim non-attendance and book make-up lessons 

  * Track your GOswim learning pathways and progression 

  * Send and receive messages to the Centre staff 




What our short video on all the things Active World will allow you to do! 

  
Download the app to login or sign up - use the code **TOMAREE**

[Download the app](http://qrco.de/bbRx0F)

## 

### GET STARTED AS AN EXISITING MEMBER 

As an existing member, we have set you up using the email you provided us upon joining â€“ **all you have to do is reset your password!**

If you are currently using Active World for your GOswim lessons â€“ all you need to do is update the app! 

1\. [Download ](http://qrco.de/bbRx0F)the Active World App 

2\. Use the facility code**TOMAREE**

3\. Select **forgot password** to reset your account â€“ follow the prompts 

4\. Login once ready and create your quick access code â€“ 4 digits 

5\. Now you're in! Check your programs or book into a new class! 

  
Watch this quick video on how to set up your app 

### GET STARTED AS A NEW MEMBER 

Looking to join our community! WELCOME! 

It's super easy to get you started! 

1\. [Download ](http://qrco.de/bbRx0F)the Active World App and select Sign Up  
  
2\. Use the facility code **TOMAREE**

3\. Create your quick access code â€“ 4 digits 

4\. Now you're in! 

5\. Click Buy Membership - Select your preference 

6\. Follow the prompts to get started! 

For more information about specific memberships or class bookings see our FAQs below. 

Watch this quick video on how to join! 

##

##  Frequently Asked Questions Expand all 

#####  Does the App work on iPhones and Android? 

Yes, it sure does! You can download the Active World App from the App Store or the Google Store.

[Download App ](http://qrco.de/bbRx0F)

If you are using a different device, you can login to your portal view the web link here https://blau.activeworld.com.au/

#####  I am creating an account, but it says an account already exists. 

If you are already a member with us, we have set you up using the email you provided us upon joining â€“ all you have to do is reset your password!

This means once you reset your password and login all your membership information will be ready for you to check!

#####  How do I book into a GOswim class? 

To book yourself or your child into a GOswim lesson all you need to do is select BookWeekly Lesson from your apps home screen. Select or add the member you wish to book into a GOswim lesson. If you or your child is already in a class, it will show you available classes to book a make up lesson. If you are not a current member of GOswim, you will be asked some questions on your swim ability then recommended a class to enrol into. At this stage you will need to buy a new membership to book the class. The app will take you through the process.

#####  How do I book into an Aqua Aerobics Class? 

To book yourself into an Aqua Aerobics session all you need to do is select Book Group Fitness from your apps home screen. Select the correct date and time in which you wish to attend a class, select the class you wish to attend and click continue. You will then be asked to select the person you wish to book into that class. If your membership includes access to classes, you will be able to see all classes available and book in. If you are not current member, you will need to go back a step and BUY a membership to book a class.

#####  My childrenâ€™s memberships are not showing in my account. 

If you have multiple memberships with us in the centre â€“ this could be yourself and your children, you should be able to see them within your account. If you cannot, please talk to our team next time you are in the centre or message us on the app to check the email address you have used to login is the primary email on all your memberships. If your child is not currently a member, you can sign them up in the app.

#####  Can I add my partner or a relative to my account? 

Yes, you can! If you would like to share your child's GOswim or other program progress with a family member, you can add them as a relative. From the home screen of the app, click on the 3 lines in the top left-hand corner (next to our centre logo). This will bring up the task bar on the left of your screen. Now select â€œMY RELATIVESâ€ - you are able to view, add or remove relatives. Once added to your profile, the relative can download the app onto their phone and login using the same information on the relative profile (the email address you used). They will be able to see everything except personal details and account information

#####  How do I contact the centre on the app? 

We have made sure that we are only the click of a button away should you need to contact us! All you have to do is select â€œMESSENGERâ€ from the home screen or the task bar to chat with our team.

#####  How do I update my billing details? 

We understand billing details need to be easy to update and change! So, we have made it simple! From the home screen of the app, click on the 3 lines in the top left-hand corner (next to our centre logo). This will bring up the task bar on the left of your screen. Select â€œMY BILLING DETAILSâ€ scroll down to 'My Billing Details'. Select â€œEDITâ€ at the top of any section you wish to update your details in â€“ don't forget to hit SAVE!

#####  What are â€˜My Awardsâ€™? 

Awards are given when you or your child reach a milestone! Mostly used in our GOswim program, you or your child will be able to see all the achievements and what they can work towards!

#####  What is â€˜Pathwayâ€™? 

The Pathway feature will give you a map view of how far you or your child have come in thier GOswim program! It will show you what levels are next and what learning outcomes need to be achieved to progress.

#####  My email address has changed, how do I update it? 

Login to your app and update your email address on your personal profile page.

#####  Is the app free? 

It sure is!

#####  I just changed my class day/time however the app has our original day/time listed. 

The App and Active World sync in live time. If your class day is showing incorrectly in your schedule, please contact the centre to ensure you are booked into the correct class.

#####  My App doesnâ€™t show the update. 

Anyone with an IOS (Apple) you just need to update your device.

If you don't have auto update selected Go to APP Store -> Click Today (Bottom Left Hand Side) -> Click your profile pic (top right hand side) -> scroll down to active world app and click update.

# Swim Club

## 

## Nelson Bay Swim Club

_"Building a Tradition one stroke at a time"_

Our home is Tomaree Aquatic Centre.

Nelson Bay Swim Club is registered with Swimming NSW the governing body for swimming in New South Wales

We are one of the oldest swim clubs in the Coast and Valley Region. At Nelson Bay SC we are interested not only in the development of swimming as a sport but also in how swimming can help develop young people. With our purpose to promote and nurture our Members in the Sport of Swimming

Nelson Bay SC we enourage not only participation on club nights but swimmers progressing within their ability to include Development Meets, Regional Carnivals, Caost & Valley Championships, Country , State Age & National Championships. We aim to inspire each swimmer to reach their full swimming potential.

Our Competitive swimmers compete all year round, in two seasons:

Summer (long Course) from October to April

Winter (Short Course) May to September

We are a not for profit organisation with all monies raised through sponsorship, fees and fundraising reimbursed back into the club and swimmers  


## Features

NBSC is an amateur club located 2 hours north of Sydney and just 40 minutes north of Newcastle on the New South Wales Coast.  
  
Our club caters for all needs from beginners at our Friday night club nights to elite age group swimmers all the way through to Masters swimmers.  
  
To express your interest please send email to :  
[presidentnbsc@gmail.com](mailto:presidentnbsc@gmail.com)

# Squad 

## 

## Tomaree Aquatic Centre Swim Squad

Our Squad aims to train the swimming champions of the future! Our squad program consists of distinct levels, arranged according to your swimming abilities.   
  
Squad levels are set to cater for recreational swimmers, improving their stroke technique and fitness, right up to elite swimmers competing in National Championship competitions.

## Levels Offered

  * Bronze Squad - $36.00 per week 
  * Silver Squad - $41.00 per week
  * Gold Squad - $45.00 per week

# Aqua Aerobics

## 

## Aqua Aerobics Classes

Aqua aerobics classes are a great way to stay fit without aggravation or risking injury. Using the resistance of water automatically increases the intensity of any movement you make, helping to increase strength, flexibility and your overall health.  
  
Aqua exercise is similar to using weights or machines in a gym, however, aqua aerobics uses the natural buoyancy of the water to help protect the body from injury whilst exercising.  
  
This also makes aqua aerobics fantastic for targeting particular areas of the body that require attention. 

## Professional Instructors

Our professional group fitness instructors provide quality instructing to motivate you to work out to the best of your ability.  
  
With a wealth of knowledge and experience our group fitness instructors are sure to inspire you to achieve your fitness goals in a fun way!  
  
Water aerobics classes are taken in a safe, friendly and relaxing environment - we are accommodating to all ages and abilities in our onsite swimming pools.

## The Benefits

Water aerobics assists in the management of injuries and rehabilitation, allowing you to exercise the body without putting stress on your joints.  
  
Evidence supports the effectiveness of hydrotherapy for managing pain and stiffness, particularly back, hip, knee and shoulder pain.  
  
Including arthritis and other chronic and complex conditions which make it hard to move.

  * Burn calories
  * Build endurance
  * Increase flexibility
  * Reduce stress on joints
  * Increase muscle strength
